-- Russia January-August net capital flight $52 billion: Economy Minister
-- 
-- Thu Sep 20, 2012 7:25am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/20/us-russia-economy-outflow-idUSBRE88J0HJ20120920

 

 MOSCOW  (Reuters) - Russia saw a net capital outflow of around $52 billion in January-August, Economy Minister Andrei Belousov said on Thursday. 
 The Economy Ministry forecasts that some $60 billion in capital will flee Russia this year. The Central Bank estimates net capital outflow in 2012 at $65 billion. (Reporting by Oksana Kobzeva and Lidia Kelly)